==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boron
<hw>Bo"ron</hw> <pr>(b⟦omac⟧"r⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Borax</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nonmetallic element
occurring abundantly in borax. It is reduced with difficulty to the free
state, when it can be obtained in several different forms; viz., as a
substance of a deep olive color, in a semimetallic form, and in
colorless quadratic crystals similar to the diamond in hardness and
other properties. It occurs in nature also in boracite, datolite,
tourmaline, and some other minerals. Atomic number 5. Atomic weight
10.81. Symbol <it>B</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>boronic</ent>⟦br⟧
